Picture this scenario: a dubiously clever man of 48, driven to the fury of his sexual Museum by an unsuccessful staircasing plan he implemented to extract more funds from his long-suffering wife in clear violation of law (his divorce lawyer should have won 700k to cover fees and punitive damages for what can only be described as a cynical abuse of litigation). This man seeks a quick divorce so that he can marry a 22 year old Romanian dancer so brilliant of foot that she has her own club chanter to encourage punters to dive into the cheese emporium of articles at her website.

After an exhausting period laden with frustration, tears (on his point of view anyway) and sweat (also from him); this man thinks, “damn it, it’s not fair. Her problem is her curfew. So why should I be the one who suffers while she is at home watching Housewives of the US? No, the laws of justice state that she should be the one who cannot sleep while I do travail in Istanbul for 15 days on end. Then she should miss out on Facebook, Twitter and Google, plus the online advantage of foundations of belonging.” And so the Diyus was invented.
